# WSL Setup Guide

This guide explains how to install WSL (Windows Subsystem for Linux) and Ubuntu 22.04 LTS on Windows.

---

# System Requirements

- Windows 10 Version 2004 or higher
- Windows 11
- Internet connection
- Virtualization enabled in BIOS

---

# Step 1: Check Windows Version

Press:

```bash
Windows + R
```

Type:

```bash
winver
```

and press Enter.

---

# Step 2: Enable Virtualization

1. Open Task Manager:

```bash
Ctrl + Shift + Esc
```

2. Go to:

- Performance
- CPU

3. Check:

```text
Virtualization: Enabled
```

If disabled:
- Restart PC
- Enter BIOS
- Enable:
  - Intel VT-x
  - AMD-V / SVM Mode

---

# Step 3: Open PowerShell as Administrator

1. Open Start Menu
2. Search:

```powershell
PowerShell
```

3. Right click:
- Run as administrator

---

# Step 4: Enable WSL Feature

Run:

```powershell
dism.exe /online /enable-feature /featurename:Microsoft-Windows-Subsystem-Linux /all /norestart
```

---

# Step 5: Enable Virtual Machine Platform

Run:

```powershell
dism.exe /online /enable-feature /featurename:VirtualMachinePlatform /all /norestart
```

---

# Step 6: Restart System

Restart your PC after enabling features.

---

# Step 7: Install WSL

Open PowerShell as Administrator and run:

```powershell
wsl --install
```

---

# Step 8: Set WSL 2 as Default

Run:

```powershell
wsl --set-default-version 2
```

---

# Step 9: Install Ubuntu 22.04 LTS

Run:

```powershell
wsl --install -d Ubuntu-22.04
```

---

# Step 10: Create Username and Password

After installation completes:

```text
Enter new UNIX username:
```

Enter your username and password.

---

# Step 11: Update Ubuntu

Run:

```bash
sudo apt update
sudo apt upgrade -y
```

---

# Step 12: Verify Installation

Run:

```powershell
wsl -l -v
```

Expected output:

```text
NAME            STATE           VERSION
Ubuntu-22.04    Running         2
```

---

# Useful WSL Commands

| Command | Description |
|---|---|
| `wsl` | Start WSL |
| `wsl --shutdown` | Stop WSL |
| `wsl -l -v` | List distributions |
| `wsl --update` | Update WSL |
| `exit` | Exit Ubuntu |

---

# Troubleshooting

## WSL Closes Automatically

Run:

```powershell
wsl --shutdown
wsl --update
```

Restart your PC.

---

## Check WSL Status

```powershell
wsl --status
```

